Thanks. Great stuff. Olu, I filled in the form and can do an hour or so tomorrow on verification<div><br></div><div>I remember how helpful you were during the Kenyan elections and many other ushahidi community activities.</div><div><br></div><div>Hope to see others online</div><div><br></div><div>Heather </div><div><br><br>On Friday, March 27, 2015, Angela Oduor Lungati &lt;<a href="mailto:angela@...">angela@...</a>&gt; wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex"><div dir="ltr"><p style="font-size:13px;margin:0.7em 0px;padding:0px;line-height:18.2000007629395px;font-family:&#39;Helvetica Neue&#39;,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif"><font color="#000000">Hello Folks!</font></p><p style="font-size:13px;margin:0.7em 0px;padding:0px;line-height:18.2000007629395px;font-family:&#39;Helvetica Neue&#39;,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif"><font color="#000000">We’ve seen a couple of deployments pop up over the last few weeks to help map the Nigerian General Elections. Olu and his team at Connected Development (CODE) have been working on Uzabe – <a href="https://uzabe.crowdmap.com/" rel="nofollow" style="text-decoration:none" target="_blank">https://uzabe.crowdmap.com</a> and need some help around Reports management and Geolocation.</font></p><p style="font-size:13px;margin:0.7em 0px;padding:0px;line-height:18.2000007629395px;font-family:&#39;Helvetica Neue&#39;,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif"><font color="#000000">They’ve done a good job outlining what <a href="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1x43WFPy3WD6a8QFVMHzAbCFzisYool6OeR-Gw8evI28/edit#slide=id.p3" style="text-decoration:none" target="_blank">their workflow is here</a></font></p><p style="font-size:13px;margin:0.7em 0px;padding:0px;line-height:18.2000007629395px;font-family:&#39;Helvetica Neue&#39;,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif"><font color="#000000">If you’re interested in volunteering, <a href="http://goo.gl/forms/db0KCrnhvG" style="text-decoration:none" target="_